Commentary.Commentary: The players are back out in the middle. Jeet Raval and Tom Latham are the openers for New Zealand. It is that man who has a terrific record with the red ball and white ball but it escalates even higher with the pink. Mitchell Starc. To Jeet Raval. Three slips and a gully in place. Let's play.

Do Australia have enough? Ian Smith mentioned before Lunch that 350 is a good score on this track. The pitch does look a bit on the slower side but that makes it equally difficult for the bowlers to take wickets. Having said that, twilight period is approaching and the Aussies will be hoping for 3-4 wickets by Stumps. Join us back at 6 pm local (1000 GMT).

Neil Wagner is caught for a quick chat on his way back. He says that it's been pretty hard and tough conditions and praises the boys for fighting it out. Credits the Australians for batting well. Smiles and tells that the push-up (after the Lunch break) was to keep himself going and being nicely warmed up as you tend to get stiff during the break.

A tough, tough 5 sessions for the visiting side. They found nothing in the heat, right from Thursday and only under lights, did they find some movement with the pink ball. That was the time when they got Matthew Wade last evening but other than that and the Warner catch, it has all been poor shot selection from the Aussies. But Wagner toiled hard, totally deserving his 4 wickets while Southee got some cheap ones towards the end. Sadly for the Kiwis, Santner was unimpressive and they did miss Lockie Ferguson today.

How does it feel when you are tired, waiting for the innings to end and then finally drag yourself off the field? And then when you see that your mates, who are not even in the playing XI, are there at the boundary line, ready to receive you with a big smile? Just lifts your spirits, doesn't it? That is how this Kiwi team is.

OUT! Caught behind! No 5-fer for Wagner, no declaration from Australia because they have been bowled out. A short ball, down the leg side, Paine looks to pull but he is cramped for room. The ball takes the glove and BJ Watling dives to his left to take the catch. He appeals and umpire Aleem Dar raises his finger. Paine does not bother reviewing and the innings ends at last. 416 IS WHAT AUSTRALIA HAVE MANAGED. TEA AS WELL ON DAY 2.
BEATEN! Beauty of a delivery. On a good length and just outside off, Paine looks to defend but misses it.
Josh Hazlewood is the last man in. 6 minutes to Tea. But it will be extended if Australia do not get bowled out before the scheduled Tea break.

OUT! Caught! That is a good catch from Colin de Grandhomme and Wagner has his fourth! A short ball, outside leg, from over the wicket, Lyon looks to pull but this time gets a bit of a top edge. The ball flies in the air and de Grandhomme at fine leg slides to his right and takes a good catch as the ball was coming at pace.
BEATEN! Full delivery outside off, Lyon looks to drive but misses it.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Nathan Lyon. Short of a length delivery on leg, Lyon pulls it over fine leg for a boundary.
FOUR! Good shot. Short delivery on leg, Lyon pulls it over square leg for a boundary.
Full delivery on off again, Lyon keeps it out.
Full delivery on off, Lyon defends it back towards the bowler.
Nathan Lyon is the next batsman in.

OUT! Caught! Starc holes out now. Finally someone is there to take a catch. Great take from a great player. Kane Williamson. After spending 145 overs in the field, you do this. Rephrase. EVEN after spending so much time on the field, you do this. Full and outside off, angling away, Starc looks to go over the bowler but the bat turns in his hands and he ends up skewing it. The ball goes off the top edge high in the air. It looks like it will land safely but Williamson covers good ground to his right from mid off, keeps his eyes on the ball and then slides to take a stunner. Superb. Starc's cameo ends but the innings doesn't. Australia continue to bat.
Outside off, Starc shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on off, Starc drives it back towards the bowler.
Length delivery on off, Starc lofts it over covers. The batsmen get two runs.
WIDE! Bowls a bouncer outside off, Starc lets it sail through to the keeper. The umpire gives it wide for height.
On a good length on leg, Starc looks to flick but misses it and gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head.
Outside off, Starc offers no shot to this one.
Full again on middle, Starc looks to flick but gets an inside edge. It goes towards the leg side. The batsmen cross ends.
Full delivery on off, Starc plays it back towards the bowler.
On a length on off, Starc guides it to short third man.
Full delivery on middle, Starc drives it back towards the bowler.
Bowls a bouncer, Starc lets it sail through to the keeper.
Full delivery on off, Paine drives it towards mid off. The fielder goes for a direct hit at the bowler's end but misses it. The batsmen manage to take a single.
Neil Wagner is back on! He has been the best bowler for the Kiwis. Can he take a 5-fer?
Outside off, Mitchell leaves it alone.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Starc looks to cut but misses it.

DROPPED! When it is not going, it is definitely not going for you. Jeet Raval has been having a torrid time with the bat and now, drops a sitter. Is the possible declaration going on in his mind? Length delivery on middle, Starc looks to loft but hits it straight to mid on. Jeet Raval tries to take the catch, gets to it but then spills it.
On a good length on off, Starc defends it to point off the back foot.
Length delivery on off, Starc plays it towards mid off.
Bowls a bouncer, Starc ducks under it.
Floated delivery on off, Mitchell plays it towards point for a single.

SIX! WHACK! Making hay while the sun shines. Starc is getting into the groove. Full and around off, plenty of flight. Starc gets down and slogs it over long on. There is a fielder over there but no problem. Mitch has enough power. 400 UP FOR AUSTRALIA.
Full delivery on off, Paine drives it towards mid off for a run.

'I AM SORRY!' says Starc. Floated delivery on middle, Paine drives it towards mid on. Santner dives to his right but cannot stop the ball. Now, Paine comes halfway down the track for the single but Starc is busy looking at the mid on fielder. Now he looks back at Paine who indicates that it was his call and he should have run.
Short on off, Starc slaps it towards covers. The batsmen take a single.
Tossed up delivery on off, Starc defends it off the front foot.
Good length delivery on off, Paine defends it out.
Outside off, Paine lets it go.

FOUR! STOP THE PRESS! Tim Paine has scored a boundary. It has been a yawning session of batting from Australia, led by their skipper. That is just his second boundary in the 98 balls that he has faced. Nice shot though. On a length, outside off, Paine rocks back and punches it late, behind point. Sweeper cover is there but before he can sweep across, the ball meets the fence.
Short delivery outside off, Starc cuts it through point for a run.
On a good length on middle, Starc defends it off the back foot.
Length delivery on middle, Paine flicks it through square leg. The batsmen take a single.
Tim Southee is back into the attack! 27-6-84-2 are his figures so far.
FOUR! Nice shot. Loopy delivery on middle, Starc plays a slog sweep over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Tossed up delivery on off, Mitchell defends it off the back foot.
Floated delivery on off, Paine plays it towards point. The batsmen cross ends.
Short delivery on off, Starc cuts it through point. The batsmen take a single.
Flighted delivery on middle, Starc defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Starc pushes it back towards the bowler.
Flatter delivery on middle, Tim defends it out of the back foot.
Full delivery outside off, Starc drives this to cover and picks up a single.

FOUR! Just inside from being a six! Flighted delivery on off, Starc bends and then lofts this towards the deep mid-wicket region for a boundary. That part of the boundary is quite long and that is the reason for the ball not going over the ropes. Colin de Grandhomme is stationed there but he is standing few metres ahead of the boundary fence making it difficult for him to reach it on time.
Flatter delivery on middle, Starc flicks it towards mid-wicket but for no runs.
Loopy ball on middle, Starc blocks it out.
Full delivery on off, Mitchell pushes it back to the bowler.
Floated on middle, Paine bends on his knees and then plays the paddle sweep to fine leg and picks up a couple.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
OHH! Flighted delivery down the leg side, Paine looks to sweep it but misses it. The Kiwis appeal for caught behind but the umpire shakes his head.
Quicker delivery on off, Paine pushes it out to cover. Santner thought there was pad first but the umpire says no.
Floated ball on off, Paine pushes it back to the bowler.
Floated ball on off, Starc flicks it to mid-wicket and takes a single.
Full delivery on middle, Paine defends it back to the bowler.
Floated ball on off, Starc attempts to defend it but it goes off the outside edge past the slip cordon. The batters take a single.
On off, defended out to cover.

FOUR! Just wide of Colin de Grandhomme. Flighted ball on off, Starc goes down on his knees and then plays the slog sweep towards deep mid-wicket where de Grandhomme is stationed but it is just wide of him. The ball goes for a boundary and Starc gets his first one of his innings.
Another flat one on middle, Starc tucks it to square leg.
Flatter delivery on middle, Starc plays it back to the bowler.
Played through mid-wicket by the batsman. The batsmen have run through for a single.
Down the leg side, Tim looks to flick but misses and is hit on the pads. A leg bye taken.
Full and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Around off, defended watchfully.

EDGED, BUT NO ONE TAKES IT! Frustration for New Zealand. Fractionally short outside off, Paine rocks back and looks to cut. But he is too close to the ball. It takes the outside edge and goes behind. But Watling is wrong-footed, moving to his left. The ball goes to his right and Ross Taylor at first slip is a bit wide. The strawberry goes right in between them to the third man fence before it is cut off. Two runs taken.
Outside off, punched off the back foot.
Full and outside off, pushed through mid off for a single.
Around middle, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.

DRINKS! It has been a sedate hour of play for Australia after Lunch. They have not added many runs after the break and just before Drinks, Cummins was bowled around the legs. New Zealand will be happy with this hour. They were good in their lines and lengths and even got the wicket of Pat Cummins. Mitchell Starc is the next man in.

OUT! BOWLED! MAIDEN TEST WICKET FOR JEET RAVAL! And more than him, Watling is happy. What happened there? Cummins has been bowled around the legs. A flighted ball down the leg side which spins from leg towards middle stump, Cummins looks to sweep it but fails to get any bat on it. The ball goes around his legs and hits the stumps. An annoying stand comes to an end. Can the Kiwis finish Australia off before Tea?
Outside off, pushed to deep cover for a single.
Full delivery around off, Paine drives it to cover for nothing.
BEATEN! Beautifully bowled! Raval flights this one outside off, Paine attempts to drive it but fails to make any connection to it.
Fuller again on middle, Cummins defends it out.
Full on middle, Pat pushes it back to the bowler.
BEATEN! Quicker delivery at 92.1 kph outside off, Cummins looks to defend it but misses it.
On middle, defended back to Santner.
Tossed up ball on middle, Cummins works it to mid-wicket.
Floated ball on middle, Cummins defends it back to the bowler.
On middle, Paine pushes it to mid on.
Full delivery on middle, Cummins works it to mid-wicket and takes a single.
This time bowls a short one on off, PC guides it to point.
Raval keeps bowling full on off, Cummins keeps pushing it to the off side.
On off, pushes this towards cover.
Full delivery on middle, Pat works it to mid-wicket.
Flatter delivery outside off, Cummins drives this to deep cover and picks up a single.
Flatter delivery outside off, Pat lets the ball go to the keeper.
BEATEN! Flighted ball outside off with some spin on it, Cummins looks to defend it but misses it.
Short ball on middle and leg, Cummins pulls it to backward square leg and picks up a couple before the fielder can come across and clean it up.
Tossed up ball on off, Cummins defends it to point.
Flatter delivery outside off, Cummins lets the ball go to the keeper.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
Full delivery around off, Cummins drives it to mid off and takes a quick single.
Fullish ball on off, pushed to cover.
Flatter delivery on off, Cummins pushes it to mid off.
Shorter delivery outside off, Cummins punches this to deep cover and picks up a single.
Floated ball outside off, Paine lets the ball go to the keeper.
Full delivery on middle, Cummins solidly defends it.
Flatter delivery outside off, Cummins lets the ball go to the keeper.
Outside off, left alone by Pat.
Flatter delivery outside off, Cummins lets the ball go to the keeper.

EDGED, FOUR! Sob. Something which is rare in this Test match. An event ball. Full and outside off, Cummins lunges out to push away from his body. The ball spins, turns, bounces and takes the outside edge. But it goes past slip and beats Jeet Raval at short third man.
Floats this one up on off, Cummins blocks it to point.
Short ball on middle, Pat tucks it to mid-wicket and picks up a single.
Flatter delivery on middle, Cummins defrends it out.
Full delivery on middle, Pat works it to the leg side.
BEATEN! Flatter delivery outside off with some spin off the wicket, Cummins looks to play the cut but misses it completely.
Flatter delivery on off, Cummins blocks it out.
Floated ball outside off, Cummins shoulders arms to this one.
Shorter delivery on off, Paine defends it to point.
Outside off, left alone.
Fullish ball outside off, Cummins lunges forward and then drives it to deep cover and picks up a single.
Floated ball on middle, Cummins blocks it out solidly.
Flatter delivery outside off, Cummins lets the ball go to the keeper.
Flighted ball on middle, Cummins defends it to the bowler.

Another short one outside off, Cummins punches this to deep cover and picks up a single to keep strike for the next over. 350 UP FOR AUSTRALIA. The question is not how many more will they add, but how long will they look to bat?
Shorter in length this time outside off, Paine cuts it towards deep cover and gives Cummins the strike.

A bit puzzling strategy by Paine and Cummins. Are they batting for just time? Given by their approach, seems like Paine is looking to try and hold Australia till the twilight period. Even loose balls from Raval are going unpunished.
On middle, Paine drives it back to the bowler.
Loopy ball on off, Tim drives it to mid off for nothing.
Floated ball outside off, Paine leaves it alone.
Full delivery on off, Paine pushes it to cover.
Another flat delivery on middle, Cummins defends it out.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Flatter delivery on middle, Cummins defends it out.
Outside off, left alone.

Some spin on offer! Santner flights this one up around off, Cummins attempts to defend it but fails to get any bat on it due to the massive away spin along with the bounce. Nathan Lyon will be watching that closely.
Floated ball outside off, Cummins lets the ball go to the keeper.
Mitchell Santner is back into the attack. 24-3-82-0 are his figures so far.
On off, pushed towards mid off.
Full delivery on middle, Paine pushes this to mid off.
Full toss on off, Paine pushes it to cover.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Short delivery outside off, Paine cuts it but straight to the point fielder who collects it on the bounce.
Full delivery around off, Paine drives this wide of the deep cover region and picks up a couple. Colin de Grandhoome comes across and cleans it up.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Cummins stands tall and blocks it onto the pitch.
Slower delivery on middle and leg, Cummins works it away to leg gully.
Full delivery down the leg side, Cummins looks to flick it but misses it.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around middle stump, Cummins ducks under it.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Cummins tucks it to mid-wicket.
Full delivery outside off angling into the batsman, Pat lets the ball go to the keeper.
Flatter delivery way outside off, Paine has no problem in leaving this ball alone.
Tossed up ball on middle, Paine blocks it out.
Loopy ball on middle, Tim defends it out.
Short ball outside off, Paine plays the square cut but finds the point fielder.
BEATEN! Nicely bowled! Flatter delivery outside off with a little bit of spin on it, Paine attempts the cut shot but fails to make any connection to it.
Tossed up ball on middle, Paine whips it to mid-wicket.
Wagner bowls a full delivery outside off, Cummins lets it go to the keeper.
Full delivery on middle, Pat drives it to mid on.
Slower delivery on middle, Cummins picks it up early and then flicks it to mid-wicket.
Short ball on the middle stump line, Paine pulls it to deep square leg and takes a single.
Good length ball on off, Cummins guide it to point and crosses over for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Cummins drives this but the mid on fielder comes across and cleans it up.
Raval tosses this one up, Cummins looks to heave it away but it goes aerial. Luckily for him, it lands short of the mid on fielder. The batters take a single.
Loopy ball on middle and leg, Pat defends it back to the bowler.
Full delivery on middle, Cummins pushes it to mid on. No run.
Tossed up ball on off, Cummins is solid in his defense and does so to cover.
Another very full delivery, almost a yorker, Cummins digs it back to the bowler.
Very full delivery outside the off stump line, Paine drives this to deep cover and takes the single.
On a length outside off, Pat shoulders arms to this one. Maiden over from Wagner.
Short of a length delivery on middle, Pat blocks it out.
Wagner is sticking to the short of a length, this time he bowls it on off. Cummins is ready for it and then defends it towards point.
Short ball on middle and leg, Cummins blocks it out onto the pitch off the back foot.
Back of a length delivery on off, Cummins stands tall and defends it out.
Short ball around middle, Cummins ducks under it.
Raval tosses this one up on middle, Cummins works it to square leg and keeps the strike for the next over.
Floated ball on off, Pat defends it to cover.
Loopy ball on middle and leg, Cummins works it to mid-wicket.
Flighted ball on middle, Paine works it behind square leg for a single.
Flatter delivery outside off, Paine cuts off the back foot towards point where Santner tumbles to field the ball.
Starts with a tossed up ball outside off, Paine shoulders arms to this one.

Jeet Raval will bowl from the other end. 2-0-8-0 so far. Haven't seen too many bad balls from him, even though he is a part-timer. Very easy-to-go action, with a bit of a loop, but not much threatening either.
On middle, defended out by Cummins.
Another short one on the leg stump line, Tim pulls it to backward square leg for a single.
Short ball around middle, Paine plays the pull shot but gets a bottom edge. The ball goes on the bounce to Colin de Grandhomme at leg gully.
On a length outside off, Paine lets the ball go to the keeper.

Short ball on middle, Paine rocks on his back foot and pulls it to deep mid-wicket. The batters take off for a couple but Paine wants three. Cummins though, is not too sure and sends Paine back. The fielder at deep mid-wicket throws it to Wagner first and then throws it to Watling but by then Paine had made it back to the crease.
Wagner starts with a short ball outside off, Paine sways away from it.

We are all set to begin the second session! The Aussie skipper, Tim Paine and Pat Cummins make their way out to the middle along with the the Kiwi players. Neil Wagner to start for the visitors. Todd Astle is on the field for Lockie Ferguson.
... Day 2, Session 2 ...

Now, what is on the card for the second session? Australia are closing in on 350. They would want to play out the first hour of the session and then take the aggressive approach to score runs quickly. The Kiwis would want to remove the remaining 4 wickets as quickly as possible. Join us to find out post this Lunch break.

The day started with Labuschagne and Head starting nicely and raising a 50-run stand between them. Wagner removed Labuschagne to break the stand. Head was then joined by skipper Paine in the middle and the duo added 24 runs. However, Head fell after his 50 to Southee. Cummins then joined Paine and saw off the remaining overs to go to Lunch.

Another tough day for the Kiwi bowlers in hot and humid conditions. They have picked up a couple of wickets but with one bowler short, it has been really a toil for them. The pacers worked hard but would've hoped for some assistance from the spinners. However, Santner did not look threatening in the 4 overs he bowled.
Around off, Paine defends it out nicely. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 2.
Paine comes forward and converts this loopy ball as full toss and drives it through mid off for a run.
Full and on off, pushed through covers for a single.
Sharp turn there. Flights this one and lands it just around off. Cummins looks to drive but gets beaten as the ball turns away.

Flighted, fuller and on middle, Paine pushes it towards mid on and takes off. Cummins though is ball watching and reacts late. The fielder fires the throw towards the keeper but Pat makes his crease with a dive.
Full and around off, it is defended.
Jeet Raval to bowl the last over before Lunch. Bowled one on Day 1. Just one slip for him.
FOUR! Nice shot. Full delivery outside off, Cummins drives it beautifully through covers for a boundary.
Flighted delivery on off, Paine drives it through covers for a run.
Loopy delivery on off, Tim plays it to the off side.
Floated delivery on off, the skipper defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Paine keeps it out.
Flighted delivery on off, Paine defends it off the front foot.

Huge appeal for caught behind this time. Williamson though does not go for the review. Probably because he lost one in the last over. A good length ball, coming in sharply. Pat looks to defend but fails to make connection as the ball sneaks through and goes to Watling behind. Watling and the bowler make a loud appeal. Not out says the umpire. Southee and Watling are sure that they heard a noise but Williamson says he did not hear a thing. Replays roll in and they suggest that there was no bat involved and the noise was of the ball kissing the pocket of the trouser.
Bouncer on middle, Cummins ducks under it.
Full and around off from Southee this time. Cummins is solid in his front foot block again.
Full and outside off again. Paine this time drives it through point and picks three.
Fullish and on off this time. Paine comes on the front foot and defends it out.
Fullish length ball in the channel outside off, Paine lets it be.
Loopy delivery on middle, Cummins blocks it off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Pat keeps it out.
Floated delivery on off, Cummins defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Paine flicks it towards square leg for a single.
Tossed up delivery on off, Paine plays it to point.

NOT OUT! Impact outside off. New Zealand lose their review. A flighted ball around off, Paine comes forward to defend but misses to get hit on the front pad. Santner and the keeper appeal but not out says the umpire. Williamson after consulting the bowler opts to take the decision upstairs. Let's see what the replays show. No edge, confirms Snicko. Now, the Ball Tracker. Here it comes, well, impact is outside off. Forget about where it hits then. Paine stays.

Huge shout for LBW! Umpire Nigel has a long look but says nothing. Williamson signals for the review after a chat with his mates. Inside edge? Impact? Here comes Snicko. No inside edge. Ball Tracker shows the impact to be outside off. Review lost. Looked close to the naked eye.
Outside off on a good length, it is left alone.
Fuller and on off, driven back to the bowler firmly.
Good length ball around off, Cummins stays on the back foot and pushes it towards gully.
Full and on off again, it is defended towards point.
Full and around off for Cummins first up. He is up for the challenge as he drives it firmly but straight to mid off.
Pat Cummins is the next batsman in.

OUT! Drilled straight to the cover fielder. Head departs after playing a handy knock though. A full ball outside off, asking for the drive. Head obliges and connects it well but it goes straight to Santner. He cannot believe it as he goes off. They check for the front foot no ball but Southee is fine. A deserving second wicket for Southee.
Full and outside off, Paine looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and rolls towards point.
Another quick run but this time for Travis Head. Floated delivery on middle, Head drives it towards mid on. The batsmen cross ends.
Flighted delivery on off, Head defends it out.
Tossed up delivery on off, Travis drives it to covers.
Quick single for the skipper. Floated delivery outside off, Paine drives it towards covers.
FOUR! First boundary for the skipper. Full delivery outside off, Paine drives it through covers for a boundary.
Around off, Head defends it out.
FOUR! Fullish ball outside off, Head cuts it through point nicely. Jeet Raval from deep mid-wicket hares to his right, makes a spirited effort to stop the ball but he is unsuccessful in doing so.
Another fuller ball, this one comes in after pitching outside off. Head covers his stumps and lets it be.
Shot but straight to the cover fielder. Full and just outside off, Head strokes it nicely but straight to the fielder.
In the channel outside off, Head lets it be.
Starts with a fuller ball outside off, asking the batsman to go for the drive. Head though is not interested.
Tim Southee returns. 24-5-77-1 are his numbers so far.
Shortish again and on middle, Paine pushes it back to the bowler.
Shortish ball on middle, Paine goes back and keeps it out.
Fires it on middle, Paine tucks it towards mid-wicket. Head wanted a single there but Paine was not interested.
Flatter and around off, Paine defends it out.
Another bad ball. Short and outside off, Head cuts it to deep backward point for a single.
FOUR! Fifty up for Travis Head. 7th in Test cricket. A poor start from Santner as he bowls a fuller ball down the leg side. Head sweeps it to the fine leg fence.
Spin for the first time as Mitchell Santner to bowl now. 20-3-65-0 are his figures so far. A slip and short leg in place.
Fullish and inviting the batsman for the drive. Paine is not lured as he lets it go the keeper.
Another ball outside off, Paine makes second leave in a row.
Outside off, Paine lets it be this time.
On middle, Paine tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Paine bails out at the last moment. Oh, there was a fly in front of his eyes.
Around off, pushed towards mid off.

Huge appeal for LBW but too high probably. A good length ball on middle and leg. Paine looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. Huge appeal from the Kiwis but not out says umpire Dar. The Ball Tracker rolls in and confirms it to be going over the stumps.
Another ball down the leg side. Another attempt of pull from Head. Another failure for him.
Full and on middle, flicked towards mid on.
Silly point comes on for Head. Short leg is already there for the left-hander.
Shortish around off this time, Head strokes it towards cover.
And again. It is down the leg side, Head once again flicks but makes no connection.
Down the leg side this time, Head looks to tickle it down the leg side but makes no connection.
FOUR! Nicely pulled! Bouncer on middle, Head rolls his wrists and pulls it between the legs of Aleem Dar at square leg and past the diving Raval at squarish mid-wicket.
Around off, this time Paine pushes it towards cover.
Make that fourth leave in a row as this one is on a length and outside off.
Gets closer to the off pole but Paine has his stumps covered as he shoulders arms.
Another leave as Paine lets it be once again.
Outside off, left alone.
Fullish and on the pads, Paine flicks it towards deep mid-wicket. It is not from the middle of the bat. The mid-wicket fielder hares after it and returns the ball but cannot stop a couple of runs.
Another bumper! Head ducks under it.
Another back of a length ball. This time the line is right. He defends it out nicely.
Another ball down the leg side. Second one from the over. Seems like Wagner has lost the trajectory. Head lets it be.
Bouncer and around off, Head sways away from it.
Low full toss around off, Head flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Wagner bowls down the leg side again. Head looks to pull but misses out.
Outside off again, Head this time lets it be.
Around off, Head taps it towards point.

RUN OUT CHANCE MISSED! Direct hit and Head would have been on his way. Outside off, Head looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto his pads. The ball rolls towards point and Head wants a single but Paine sends him back. Henry Nicholls charges in from backward point, gets to the ball and has a shy at the stumps at the striker's end with Head halfway down the track. However, he is not quite able to adjust to the angle and misses by a big margin. Concedes an overthrow as the ball goes towards fine leg.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Play and a miss! Fullish length and outside off, Head feels for the ball as he goes for the drive but misses.
Fullish length ball outside off, Head lets it be.
Good length ball around off and middle, Paine blocks it back to the bowler nicely.
Good length and around off, Paine pushes it towards mid on.
Shortish length and around off, Paine taps it towards cover.
On the pads again, Head tucks it nicely past the short leg fielder behind square leg for a single.
Down the leg side this time. Head lets it be.
Shortish length outside off, Head looks to cut but gets an inside edge onto the pads.

Drinks! Labuschagne and Head almost saw off the first hour of play. There's hardly any life on the wicket but Wagner bowled the shortish length with venom. However, the Aussie overnight batters were up for the challenge as they played them well. Labuschagne eventually fell to Wagner just before the Drinks break. Head is looking solid out there in the middle. He has skipper Paine for company. They would look to add another partnership to take Australia towards a big first innings score. The Kiwis are already one bowler short and it seems like they will be having a tough next hour too. They would love to get a few more wickets as soon as they can and try restricting the Aussies to as low as they could. Hot and humid conditions are surely not gonna help them. Interesting hour ahead.
Good length around off, Paine defends it out.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Around off, Paine pushes it towards gully with soft hands.
Outside off, Paine shoulders arms.
Just outside off, guided towards short third man.
Full and around off, pushed towards mid off.
Just past short leg! Good bowling! Another short of length ball into the body. Head tucks it away but it was not too far from the reach of the short leg fielder.
Around off, Paine pushes it through point for a single to get off the mark.
A bouncer to welcome the skipper. It is on middle but Paine has no problem ducking under it.
Skipper Tim Paine walks out. Short leg in position.

OUT! BOWLED AROUND HIS LEGS! It is Wagner who has removed the man who has become a thorn in the flesh of the opposition pretty quickly. Sad, sad moment for Marnus Labuschagne. In spite of scoring 143? Why, do you ask? Because Labuschagne would have been only the third player after Zaheer Abbas and Mudassar Nazar to register three consecutive 150-plus scores in Test cricket! He is distraught. Not perhaps of the missed record but simply because he has been denied an opportunity to bat throughout the day. A bit of his own doing, one would say. Labuschagne walks across his stumps and does so pretty early. Wagner targets the stumps and does so with a fast ball. Labuschagne misses his flick and the ball hits the stumps. He just stands there dismayed and then trudges off. The whole crowd gives him a standing applause. Can New Zealand keep Australia under 375 now?
Another back of a length on middle and leg, Marnus pulls it through fine leg and gets a couple. That also brings up the 300 for Australia.
Back of a length on the hips of Head. He tucks it through square leg and gets to the other end.
Good length around off again, Labuschagne bunts it on the pitch on the off side.
On off, pushed towards point.
Outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms to this one.
Around off on a fullish length, Labuschagne flicks it again. This time it is uppish but wide of the mid-wicket fielder. A couple of runs taken.
FOUR! Whipped off the pads. Brilliant shot. Full and around off, Labuschagne flicks it nicely, using his wrists to the deep mid-wicket fence.
Full around off, driven straight to mid off.
Another bouncer, targeting the head of Head. Head does well to evade it.
Wagner bowls another one down the leg side. Head lets it be.
Down the leg side, Head looks to flick but makes no connection.
Bouncer outside off, Labuschagne pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a run.
Slightly short and on middle, Labuschagne keeps it out.
Short and around off and middle, Labuschagne pulls it wide of deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Beaten! Full and wide outside off, inviting the drive. Head falls in the trap and drives but away from the body to get beaten.
On middle, it is pushed towards mid on.
Around off and on a length, Head pushes it back to the bowler who looks to stop the ball with his right hand. However, it deflects towards mid off.
FOUR! Brilliant shot! Full and around off this time, Head gets in the position and drives it through mid off for a boundary.
Overpitched and outside off, Head drives it well but Williamson at mid off dives to his right and makes a nice stop.
Starts with a good length ball around off, Head pushes it towards mid off nicely.
Colin de Grandhomme is on now! He was the man who got New Zealand the first wicket on Day 1. Can he get one on Day 2 too? 16-6-24-1 are his figures so far.
Another shortish length, this time Head tucks it wide of short fine leg for a single.
Bouncer again but this time Marnus pulls it towards deep square leg for a run.
Bouncer around off this time, Labuschagne sways away.
FOUR! 17th boundary for Labuschagne. Wagner looking for the slower delivery dishes out a full toss. Labuschagne drives it through mid on firmly and it wins the race against the mid on fielder.
Shortish length around off, Marnus taps it towards the off side of the back foot.
Short ball down the leg side, actually way down the leg side. Labuschagne lets it be.
On the pads, Labuschagne tucks it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Around off and middle, Labuschagne pushes it towards mid on.
Outside off again and slightly shortish length. Head cuts it to deep point for a single.

FOUR! Good effort but in vain. A shortish length ball outside off, Head cuts it nicely towards deep point. Santner from deep cover hares to his right and makes a sliding attempt to stop the ball. He does so but not cleanly and the ball eventually touches the fence. 50-run stand is up between Travis Head and Marnus Labuschagne.
Shortish ball around off and middle, Labuschagne tucks it towards fine leg. Labuschagne wanted the second but Wagner was quick to get around and stop the second.
FOUR! Shot of the morning so far! Just overpitched from Southee. Labuschagne leans forward and drives it to the long on fence nicely.
On middle, Head tucks it nicely but straight to Latham at short leg.
Behind good length and around off, Head taps it back to the bowler.
Bouncer again but this time Labuschagne goes for the pull and turns it towards deep square leg for a run.
Another one but this one is way too high to make the batsman play. Marnus ducks under it.
Bouncer around off again, Labuschagne sways away from it nicely.
Sharp bouncer! But no close in fielder on the off side. A silly point could've made things interesting. Back of a length ball around off, Labuschagne hops and blocks towards point uppishly.
Full and just around off, Head drives it to mid off firmly.
Full and around off and middle. Head pushes it towards mid on.
Full and around off, Head looks to drive but manages to hit it off the toe end of the bat towards cover.
Around off, Head pushes it towards mid-wicket.
In the channel outside off, Head makes a leave.
FOUR! Nicely done! Another ball on the pads, this time Head guides it towards the fine leg fence nicely. Had there been a leg gully, Head would've been on his way.
Outside off, Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Another shortish length ball on middle and leg, Head looks to tuck it towards fine leg but cannot make the connection right. The ball goes to left of the short leg fielder for a single.
Bouncer and around off, Head hops and keeps it out nicely.
A switch of fielders. Jeet Raval, who was at leg gully, swaps positions with the man at deep mid-wicket. There is a short leg in place as well, so expect plenty of short stuff.
Back of a length ball down the leg side. Head looks to tickle it fine but misses. Was not too far from tickling the gloves there.
On middle, Head strokes it straight to mid on.

Good length ball around middle, Labuschagne looks to defend but it goes towards leg gully off the inner half. A late call for the single there. The fielder gets to the ball and fires a throw at the non-striker's end but misses. Direct hit could've been interesting.
Full and on middle, Labuschagne drives it wide of mid on for a single.
FOUR! First one of the day! Overpitched and outside off, Labuschagne leans into the drive and creams it through covers for a boundary.

Nicely punched! Slightly shortish length outside off, Head goes on the back foot and punches it through cover and point. Nicholls and Wagner go after the ball. Nicholls slides in and flicks the ball towards Wagner who return is back to the keeper. Three runs taken.
Beautifully bowled but equally well played by Head. Southee pitches it outside off and makes it come back in sharply. Head gets his bat down in time to defend it out.
Back of a length ball on middle, Labuschagne rides the bounce and pulls it by rolling the wrists. The ball goes behind square leg for a single.
In the channel outside off again, Labuschagne lets it be.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Around off, Head comes forward and keeps it out.

Not from the middle of the bat but three runs and it brings 250 up for Australia. Fuller length and outside off, Marnus goes for the drive but manages a thick outside edge which goes through point for three.
Double bluff? Wagner dishes a good length ball outside off, Labuschagne lets it be.

A change in the field. Wagner is switching to around the wicket and perhaps is targetting the short ball. He has a chat with skipper Williamson and sends mid-wicket back to the fence. Moves point as well, to the place where short mid-wicket was.
Full and wide outside off. Head unlike Labuschagne wants to feel the ball as he drives and picks a single towards wide of mid off. Australia are underway for the day.
Wagner starts with a fuller length ball on off for the left-hander. Head pushes it back to the bowler.
Neil Wagner it will be from the other end. 22-4-52-2 so far. A real workhorse this lad is. Took a stunning caught and bowled and kept on running in the whole day.
Misses the line this time does Southee as he sprays down the leg side. Labuschagne misses his flick too.
Another good leave. This one probably on the length too. In the channel again, it just comes in but not enough to strike on the pads. Goes straight to the keeper.
Closer to off pole again, just behind good length. Labuschagne has his timbers covered as he lets it go the keeper.
Outside off again and on a good length. Labuschagne is not going after these this early as he shoulders arms.
This time he gets closer to the off pole. Labuschagne comes forward and blocks it out solidly.
Southee starts with a ball in the channel outside off and on a good length. Labuschagne lets it be, in his own style.

We are all set for the day to begin. Labuschagne and Head are ready to go out onto the field, standing at the ropes. Head just has a feel of the Aussie flag with his left hand and from behind, comes Labuschagne. They both have a chat and now, Head goes out. Labuschagne, on the other hand, waits, does some situps, mutters some words to himself and follows his partner. Now, the Kiwis follow suit. The first 20-30 minutes will be very crucial. Tim Southee will start off proceedings to Labuschagne. Two slips in place. 20-4-53-1 so far. Here we go!

And now, finally about New Zealand. They bowled their hearts out, on a track which had nothing much to offer with the exception of Lockie Ferguson. He seemed to go only for pace and lacked direction and control. HE HAS BEEN RULED OUT OF BOWLING IN THIS TEST, which makes the responsibility on the other bowlers even greater. The second new ball is just 10 overs old, so they would want to strike early. Southee managed to get some swing last night but was that more due to the conditions? We shall know in some time.

Steven Smith and Marnus Labuschagne - the present and the future for Australia. Almost like a master and his apprentice at work. They grinded and grinded and grinded the Kiwis amidst a 132-run stand which consumed almost 50 overs. That is close to 2 sessions. Steven Smith looked out of sorts but Labuschagne looked like a man in total control. He left the balls well, had good compact defense and also attacked the odd bad ball. Towards the end, he started to counter-attack as well and hence, his wicket would be very crucial for the Black Caps this afternoon.

In a day-night Test match, the pink ball barely swings in the afternoon and that is what exactly happened. The Kiwis struggled to generate consistent swing for long but then quickly adjusted to bowling accurate lines and lengths. Australia, on the other hand, found it tough to get going as the ball did not quite come onto the bat. But they too, did well to curb their attacking instincts and ensured that there was no collapse as such.

A day of the South Africans it was in the Australian city of Perth. Klerksdorp-born Marnus Labuschagne and Pretoria-born Neil Wagner called the shots on Thursday as Australia and New Zealand battled it out on a day of attrition. A day of old-age traditional Test cricket where there was good contest between bat and ball. New Zealand did not give an inch while Australia fought hard. In a day of frustration for both teams, no one came out clearly on top and that promises an exciting second day's play. Hello and a warm welcome.

The day has belonged to centurion Marnus Labuschagne but the match right now is tantalisingly close. The middle order of Australia has not been tested for large parts of the last series against Pakistan and New Zealand would be looking to make early inroads on Day 2. We hope for another exciting day of cricket on Friday. Do join us at 1300 Local (0500 GMT). Till then, cheers and take care!

Marnus Labuschagne on his way to the pavilion stops for an interview. He says that it was difficult in the initial phase of the innings. Mentions that the pitch is tricky to bat on and it feels good to score and bat well. He also adds that the team is in a strong position after the end of the day's play. The conditions are hot and tiring. On being asked about his achievement of becoming the joint 4th fastest Australian batsman to score 1000 Test runs, Labuschagne says that he was not aware about that record but is happy with his performance.

Wagner has certainly got to be the pick of the bowlers as he took potentially the most dangerous wickets of David Warner and Steven Smith. Tim Southee and Colin de Grandhomme also chipped in with one wicket each but a major concern for New Zealand will be that they are now one bowler short as Lockie Ferguson had gone off with a calf strain and further updates on him will be provided on the morning of Day 2.

The day started with a steady partnership between Joe Burns and David Warner. The bowling from the New Zealanders was disciplined and it reaped rewards as Joe Burns departed for just 9 runs. Warner looked confident in his innings of 43 runs but was dismissed in spectacular fashion by Wagner as he took a very good low catch off his own bowling. Steven Smith and Marnus Labuschagne then formed a 132-run stand and took the hosts to comfortable shores before Smith departed. However, the day belonged to Marnus Labuschagne who made batting look easy on a very tricky pitch where even Steven Smith struggled to find his rhythm. He will be looking to carry on from his knock of 110 runs on Day 2 and give his team a healthy advantage.

So, that will be it from Day 1 of the first Test match. It has been the day of Marnus Labuschagne who is unbeaten after scoring a ton. Australia end Day 1 on 248/4. The Australian pair of Head and Labuschagne trudge off the pitch with their heads held high and overall a decent day for the hosts.
Good length ball outside off, Head looks to defend at first but takes his bat away at the last moment. With that, it is STUMPS ON DAY 1.
Fullish ball on middle and leg, Travis works it through mid-wicket and takes a couple.
Full delivery on middle, Head blocks it out.

JUST! Short ball outside off, Labuschagne plays the upper cut but does not realize that there is a fielder placed there just for that. Luckily for Marnus, the ball fell just short of Ross Taylor at third man. This though, is brilliant captaincy from Kane Williamson.
Good length ball on middle, Labuschagne defends it to mid-wicket.
Full delivery on off, Marnus blocks it back to Wagner.
Full delivery on middle, Head defends it out to cover.
FOUR! Nicely played! Southee goes full yet again on off, Head creams the drive between cover and mid off and into the fence. Second boundary of the over.
BEATEN! Beautiful! Good length ball outside off, Head attempts to defend it but misses it completely. There was a bit of noise but Snicko shows that there was no bat on it.
FOUR! SHOT! Full delivery outside off, Head leans forward and drills the drive through covers and into the fence. Wagner puts a terrifc run in an attempt to clean it up but fails to do so.
Good length ball on middle, Marnus whips it to mid-wicket and picks up a single.

BEATEN! Southee has been excellent since they have taken the new ball. Good length ball outside off swinging away, Labuschagne looks to defend it off the back foot but the ball whizzes past the bat and into the mitts of the keeper.
Slower full delivery outside off, Travis picks it and pushes it to mid off.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around middle stump, Head ducks under it.
Short ball down the leg side, Head does not fiddle with it and lets the ball go to the keeper.
Full delivery outside off, Head drives it to cover where the fielder dives to stop the ball.
Full delivery on middle, Head defends it out.
BEATEN! Beautiful bowling! Good length delivery outside off, Head looks to defend it but fails to make any connection with it.
Full delivery on middle, Travis whips it to deep mid-wicket and takes a single.
Full delivery way outside off, Head lets the ball go to the keeper.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Good length ball on off, Travis defends it off the back foot towards cover.
FOUR! Just over! Short ball outside off, Head slashes at it and it goes just over the gully fielder and into the fence.
Good length ball outside off, Head looks to defend at first but then makes a good decison to leave that one. That took off after pitching and almost kissed the edge.
Full delivery outside off, Head attempts to drive but it goes off the inside edge to deep square leg. Head keeps the strike with a single.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Head whips it to mid-wicket.
Outside off, Head lets it go to the keeper.
Full delivery on off, Head pushes it to cover for nothing.
Good length ball on middle, Marnus works it to square leg and picks up a single.
Full delivery outside off, Labuschagne lets the ball go to the keeper.
Neil Wagner is back on. 19-3-47-2 are his figures so far.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! Full delivery outside off, Head creams the drive through covers for a boundary. He gets off the mark as well with that one.
On off, defended out.
Full delivery on off, Head drives it to mid off.
Full delivery outside off swinging in, Head makes a good leave.
The batsman works it down the leg side.

OHH! A huge shout for LBW! Good length ball on middle and leg, Head looks to shuffle and flick it but misses to get hit on the pads. Southee appeals but Aleem Dar, the umpire, shakes his head. Southee is seen asking his captain, Kane Williamson, whether it is too high. The Hawk Eye rolls in and it shows that it was going over the stumps. Good call not to review the decision.
Outside off, left alone by Marnus.
Full delivery outside off, Marnus lets the ball go to the keeper.
Fullish ball on middle, Marnus drives it but de Grandhomme jumps up and collects it.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
Good length delivery outside off, Marnus shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Labuschagne defends it out onto the pitch.
On a length on off, Head punches this off the back foot to cover.
Full delivery on middle, Travis pushes it to mid on.
Full delivery outside off which holds its line, Head first looks to defend it but decides to let the ball go to the keeper.
Good length ball on middle, Head guides it to point.
Full delivery on off, Head pushes it to mid off.
Travis Head is the new man in. He needs to arrest the Aussie slide.

OUT! TIMBER! The new ball does the trick! This is brilliant bowling from Southee but also a bad decision by Wade. Good length delivery on off, swinging in, Wade misreads the movement on it and decides to leave the ball. The ball goes on to hit the top of the off pole and the Kiwi players are ecstatic. Two quick wickets for New Zealand, one before Drinks and one after. Can they pick up more wickets before end of the day's play or will Australia hold on?
Full delivery outside off, Marnus does not fiddle with it and lets it go to BJ Watling.
Fullish delivery outside off, Labuschagne leaves it alone again.
Good length ball outside off, Marnus lets the ball go to the keeper.
Full delivery on off, Wade drives it straight to mid off and picks up a single.
On a length on middle, Matthew blocks it out.
NO BALL! Colin de Grandhomme has overstepped here. Full delivery on middle, Wade defends it back to the bowler.
Starts with a good length delivery outside off, Wade shoulders arms to this one.
Colin de Grandhomme is back on! 14-5-22-1 are his figures so far.
On a good length on middle, Marnus defends it out.
Outside off, Labuschagne does not bother to play at that.
Length delivery on off, Wade plays it towards the off side. The batsmen take a single.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Wade looks to drive but misses it due to the away movement on this one.
Outside off, Wade shoulders arms to this one. There is swing on offer with the second new ball.
On a good length on middle, Wade flicks it to mid-wicket.
80 overs have been bowled by the Kiwis and the second new ball is due. And yes, it has been taken straightaway. Tim Southee to test Wade with the strawberry.
Flighted delivery on middle, Marnus defends it off the back foot.
Floated delivery on off, Labuschagne drives it to mid off.
Short delivery on off, Wade makes room and punches it through point. The fielder chases it, slides and does well to stop it before the ropes. The batsmen get three runs.
Full delivery on off, Wade drives it to covers.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Wade offers a forward defense on this one.
FOUR! Excellent shot. Flighted delivery on middle, Wade sweeps it over square leg for a boundary.
Bowls it down the leg side, Labuschagne looks to flick but misses it.
On a good length on middle, Marnus defends it out.

IN THE AIR BUT SAFE! Short delivery outside off, Labuschagne looks to guide it over the third man region but does not time it properly. It just about goes over the fielder at short third man who tries to jump and get a hand to it but fails. The batsmen get two runs.
Length delivery on middle, Labuschagne flicks it to square leg.
On a good length on middle, Marnus nudges it towards the leg side.
Bowls a bouncer outside off, Marnus ducks under it.
WIDE! Bowls a bouncer, Labuschagne does well to duck under it. The umpire gives it wide for height.
Flatter delivery outside off, Wade pushes it to cover.
Flatter delivery on middle, Wade flicks it to mid-wicket for nothing.
On off, Labuschagne pushes it to long on and takes a single.
Short delivery outside off, Marnus pushes it to cover.
Another flat delivery on middle, Labuschagne comes down the track and defends it back to the bowler.
Flatter delivery on off, Marnus defends it back to the bowler.
Full delivery on the pads, Wade flicks it to square leg and picks up a couple. Could have been close had there been a better throw from the fielder at square leg.
Short delivery outside off, Wade sways away from it.
Slower full delivery on off, Wade sees it early and digs it out onto the pitch.
Bouncer around middle, Wade ducks under it.
Good length ball around off, Wade looks to flick it but gets an inside edge onto the pads. Wagner appeals but nothing doing says the umpire.
Full delivery on off, Wade defends it to the off side.

Drinks! It has been a good hour after the Tea break for the Aussies as Labuschagne got to his ton but the wicket of Steven Smith just before the Drinks break has given the Kiwis a window of opportunity to come back strongly. If they are able to take the wicket of Labuschagne now, they can put some real pressure on the hosts. The middle order of Australia will finally be tested but with Lockie Ferguson off with a calf injury, they have at least one less thing to worry about.
Tossed up ball on off, Marnus drives it to cover for nothing.
Floated ball on off, Marnus pushes this to cover.
On middle, blocked.
Loopy ball on middle, Wade plays the paddle sweep to fine leg and gets off the mark with that single.
Floated ball outside off, Wade lets the ball go to the keeper.
Flighted ball outside off, Marnus pushes it to cover and takes a single.
Bouncer on off, Wade does not fiddle with it.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Wade.

Almost another one goes down! Fullish ball outside off by Wagner, Wade goes for a drive on the first ball. He edges it towards Ross Taylor at first slip but the ball falls just short of him and hits Taylor on the knee. Warning early on for Matthew Wade.
Matthew Wade is the new man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Steven Smith departs and luckily for Latham, his dropped catch does not cost the Kiwis much. Another bouncer bowled on middle and leg by Wagner, Smith this time does not duck and plays the hook shot. He mistimes it a touch and the ball goes straight to Tim Southee near short backward square leg. Smith has to depart and the 132-run stand has been broken. Now it is a chance for the Kiwis to test the under-question Australian middle order. Will they be up for the task?
Bouncer on middle and leg, Smith ducks under it.
On the pads of Marnus, he flicks this one towards mid-wicket for one.

OHH! Flatter delivery around off, Smith looks to defend it but misses it to get hit on the pads. Santner and the rest put in a huge appeal for LBW but the umpire shakes his head. The Kiwis do not even think of a review.
It's been driven superbly through the covers.
Flighted ball outside off, Smith looks to drive it but misses it due to some spin on it. Ross Taylor catches it at first slip but there was no bat on it.
Floated ball on middle, Marnus flicks it to mid-wicket and takes a single.

SIX! THIRD CONSECUTIVE CENTURY! What an innings from Labuschagne. He has made some giant strides in Test cricket since he replaced Steven Smith in the Ashes as the concussion substitute. He gets there by lofting this tossed up ball on middle over the long on region for a maximum. Can he convert this to a double now?
Flatter delivery outside off, Labuschagne pushes it to cover.
Short ball down the leg side, Smith does not fiddle with it and lets it go past him.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Smith whips it to square leg.
Short ball down the leg side, Smith lets the ball go to the keeper.
BOUNCER! Smith once again ducks under it.
Wagner bowls a bouncer around off, Steven Smith ducks under it.
Short ball on the leg stump line, Marnus pulls it to deep square leg and picks up a single.
On off, driven to mid off.
Full delivery on middle, Smith drives it to mid on for nothing.
Finally we see some spin!! Santner flights this one up around off with a bit of spin and bounce, Steven comes forward to defend it but fails to put any bat on it.
Fullish on off, pushed to cover.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
Floated ball outside off, Smith drives this to cover.
FOUR! Pulled away! Short delivery on middle, Labuschagne rocks on his back foot and hammers the pull to deep square leg for a boundary.
Good length delivery on middle and leg, Marnus whips it to deep square leg and picks up a couple. 1000 runs for Marnus Labuschagne in Test cricket. Moves into the 90s as well.
Good length ball on middle, Marnus defends it back to the bowler.
On a length on off, Marnus guides it to point.
FOUR! How did he find this gap? Back of a length delivery in the channel outside off, Labuschagne runs it down between the second and third slip fielders into the fence.
Full delivery on off, Marnus defends it to mid off.
Neil Wagner has a change of ends.
Loopy ball on off, Smith drives it to cover.
Flatter delivery on off, Smith works this away towards mid-wicket and picks up a couple.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Full delivery on middle, Marnus works it to square leg and takes a single.
Another flat one outside off, ML guides it to point.
Flatter delivery outside off, Labuschagne looks to play the cut but seeing the ball was a little wide, he waits and runs it down to third man for a couple.
Mitchell Santner is back into the attack. 14-2-43-0 are his figures.

This is bad, bad news for New Zealand. Black Caps have just tweeted that Lockie Ferguson is off the field with a suspected right calf strain sustained while bowling in the second session. He is about to go for an MRI scan and will be reassessed in the morning. A bowler down in this heat, that too, this early in the series, is no good at all for the Kiwis.
Full delivery on off, Smith defends it out to mid off.
Good length delivery outside off, Steven does not fiddle with it yet again and lets the ball go to the keeper.
Outside off, left alone.
On a length outside off, Smith lets the ball go to the keeper.
Full delivery outside off, Marnus drives this to covers and picks up a single.

OHH! Good length ball on middle, Marnus looks to defend it but misses it completely. It hits Marnus flush on the pads. Southee puts in a huge appeal but nothing from the umpire. The Kiwis think of a review but decide against it. The replays roll in and Hot Spot shows that there was a bit of an inside edge on that one. Excellent umpiring from Aleem Dar.
Short ball outside off, Labuschagne ducks under it.
On off, defended out by Smith to mid off.
On a length on off, Smith defends it to the off side off the back foot.
Fullish ball outside off, Smith shoulders arms.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Smith defends it to mid on.
Full delivery outside off, Steven Smith does not fiddle with it and leaves the ball alone.
Neil Wagner is back into the attack. 13-2-30-1 are his figures so far.
Good length ball outside off, Marnus lets the ball go to the keeper.
FOUR! Beautiful, absolutely beautiful! Southee goes full on middle, Labuschagne flicks it to deep mid-wicket and picks up his 12th boundary of the innings.
On a length outside off, Marnus leaves it alone.
Fullish delivery on middle, Marnus flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball outside off, Labuschagne leaves the ball alone.
Full delivery outside off, Marnus lets the ball go to the keeper.
Tim Southee is back into the attack. 13-3-29-0, his figures so far.
Flighted ball outside off, Steven blocks it to cover.
On middle, defended.
Fullish ball outside off, Steven pushes it to cover.
Full delivery on middle, Smith drives it straight but Santner makes a good stop to his right.
Floated ball on off, Smith defends it to cover.
Flatter delivery outside off, Smith shoulders arms to this one.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length ball outside off, Marnus lets the ball go to the keeper.
Full delivery on off, Labuschagne drives this to mid off for nothing.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
On a length on middle, ML defends it back to the bowler.

FOUR! A rare bad ball. De Grandhomme drifts this one down the leg side, Labuschagne just flicks this one to fine leg for a boundary. 100-run stand up between the two. It has taken some time but it has been an excellent one after they lost two quick wickets.
Full delivery on middle, defended back to the bowler.
Santner tosses this one up on off, Smith is solid in defense.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! Flighted ball outside off, Smith leans forward and drives it through the extra cover region for a boundary.
Floated ball outside off, Labuschagne drives it towards cover and picks up a single.
Loopy ball on off, Labuschagne pushes it to cover.
Flatter delivery on off, Marnus plays it onto the pitch.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length ball on middle and leg, driven towards mid on.
Full ball on off, driven towards mid off.
Just outside off again, left alone.
Another length ball outside off, Smith blocks it.
Length ball outside off, left alone.
Fullish ball on middle, Smith drives it to mid on and takes a single. Colin de Grandhomme has a shy at the bowler's end and hits but Smith was well in.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Floated on off, Smith pushes it back to the bowler.
Fullish delivery on off, Marnus pushes it to mid off and takes a single.
Flatter delivery on the pads, Smith whips it to backward square leg and takes three. The fielder hares across and cleans it up.
Floated delivery on off, Smith lunges and defends it to cover.
Good length ball way outside off, Labuschagne lets the ball go to the keeper. Just 1 run off the last 3 overs. Kiwis tightening the screws on the Aussies.
On off, pushed towards cover.
Full delivery outside off, Marnus drives it to cover for nothing.
Good length ball outside off, Marnus shoulders arms to it.
Full on middle, driven to mid on.
Good length ball on off, Labuschagne defends it to cover.
Flighted ball on off, Smith pushes this past the diving Santner to mid off. No run.
Flatter one outside off, Steven lets it go to the keeper.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
Full delivery on middle, Smith blocks it back to the bowler.
Flatter delivery on off, Smith pushes it to covers.
Full delivery on off, Labuschagne pushes it to cover and takes a single.
Tom Latham has been moved to short leg.
Better from Smith! Full delivery on middle, Smith drives it to mid on for nothing.
OHH! Why are you playing these kind of shots, Smith? Full delivery way outside off, Steven goes for an extravagant drive but misses it completely. Could have left that ball alone.
On a length outside off, Smith lets the ball go to the keeper.
Outside off, left alone by Smith.
Fullish delivery outside off, Smith lets the ball go to the keeper.
Good length delivery on off, Smith pushes it back to the bowler.
Colin de Grandhomme to partner Santner from the other end.
Flatter delivery on middle, Smith works it to the leg side and takes a single.
Full delivery on off, Labuschagne drives it to mid off and takes a single.
Flat one on off, Marnus whips it away to mid-wicket.
Flatter delivery on middle, Smith works it to square leg and takes a single.
Loopy ball on off, Smith prods forward and blocks it to cover.
Starts with a flighted ball on middle and leg, Smith defends it back to the bowler.

The final session of Day 1 is all set to begin! Marnus Labuschagne and Steven Smith come out to resume their partnership with Mitchell Santner starting the proceedings for the Kiwis. Can the Kiwis get some quick wickets?
... Day 1, Session 3 ...

The Kiwis were good with the ball. They bowled with discipline but have been unable to find a wicket. Lockie Ferguson was denied a wicket as Tom Latham dropped a catch at second slip of Steven Smith. The Kiwis need to pick up some quick wickets and try to restrict the hosts to a low score, otherwise these two can take the game away from them. Will New Zealand fight back or will the hosts continue to churn out runs? Join us in a while to find out.

Labuschagne is happy with his knock as he feels it is very hard to score with the ball not coming on to the bat. Adds that his aim was only to bat watchfully and not throw his wicket away, adding as much as he possibly can to the team's cause.

A sedate session but an excellent one for Australia. They have not lost a wicket in this session with Marnus Labuschagne and Steven Smith going strong and have kept the visitors at bay. The former has gone onto score his fifty while Steven Smith, after a fidgety start to his innings, has started to get going in the latter stages of the session with some lovely shots. The hosts would be hoping that these two can continue after the break and get them to a good score.

Aggressive way to finish the session as Raval floats one outside off and Smith comes down the track. He drives it powerfully towards the cover region and takes a couple as the man at sweeper cover cuts it off. That will be TEA ON DAY 1!
Shortish delivery way wide outside off, Smith works it towards point and takes an easy single.
Loopy delivery on middle, driven towards mid on.
On the leg side, Labuschagne flicks it towards mid-wicket for one.
Floated on off, driven towards mid off.
Starts with a shortish delivery on middle, worked towards mid-wicket for one.
Surprising, Williamson has brought Jeet Raval into the attack.
On the hips of Marnus, he looks to flick but misses to get hit on the thigh pad.
Smith goes back deep in his crease and works it wide of cover for one.
FOUR! Smith in full flow! Flatter delivery on middle and leg, Smith comes down the ground and flicks this one beautifully in the gap between mid on and mid-wicket for a boundary.
Tossed up outside off, left alone.
On the leg side, Smith works it towards backward square leg for a quick couple.
Floated on middle, Smith prods forward and defends.
Length ball outside off, Labuschagne works this one towards point.
Full ball on middle and leg, driven towards the mid on region.
On middle and off, defended by Marnus.
Length ball on off, defended from within the crease.

FOUR! Pulled away! Back of a length ball on middle, Labuschagne rocks back and pulls this towards the mid-wicket region. Raval there dives to his left but the ball is way wide of him and the ball races away to the fence.
On the pads, worked towards the square leg region for one.
The batsman drives this to cover.
Floated on off, pushed towards cover.
Fullish ball outside off, Labuschagne creams the drive through covers and picks up a couple before Williamson can hare after it and clean it up.
Loopy ball on middle, Smith drives it straight down the ground. Santner gets a hand on it, hits the umpire and rolls to the off side. The batters pick up a single.
Very full delivery on off, Smith drives it to covers for nothing.
Floated on off, Smith blocks it out.

DROPPED! Latham is the culprit and Steven Smith has been given a life out of all people. Length ball wide outside off, Smith goes for a wild slash at it but only manages to get a thick outside edge. The ball goes to the left of second slip where Latham is positioned. He gets his left hand to it but the ball does not stick and goes behind the slip cordon. The batters steal a run. Ferguson has been denied his first international Test wicket. How costly will this prove to be for the Kiwis?
Good length ball on middle and off, pushed back towards the bowler. The man at mid off collects it.
Good bouncer by Ferguson, Smith sways away from it.
On the hips of Labuschagne, he flicks this one towards deep square leg and takes a quick three.
Length ball on middle and off, defended off the front foot.
Lockie Ferguson is back with a change of ends.
Length ball on middle, pushed down towards mid on.
Shortish on off, Smith goes back and pushes it towards the cover region.
Tossed up on middle and leg, Smith pushes this one towards the right of the bowler.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Floated on middle, defended back towards the bowler.
Loose delivery by Santner, down the leg side. Smith just nudges it fine down the leg side for a couple.
Floated on middle, Smith stylishly flicks this one towards the mid-wicket region but Nicholls there does well as he dives to his left to collect the ball.
Mitchell Santner is back into the attack. His figures are 6-1-17-0.
Full ball on middle, Marnus again drives this one back past the bowler but the man at mid off this time cuts it off.
Full ball again, this time driven towards mid on.

FOUR! One of the shots of the day by Labuschagne and runs starting to flow now. Overpitched by Southee, Labuschagne leans forward and drives this one down the ground for a boundary. Straight as an arrow!
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Length ball outside off, a slash from Labuschagne and he is well beaten as the ball whizzes past his outside edge.
Length ball on middle and off, defended out.
Full ball outside off, Smith jams it out towards the point region.
On the pads, flicked towards mid-wicket for a single.
Full ball on middle and off this time, Marnus pushes it back towards the bowler. The man from mid off jogs to his left and collects it.
Another one outside off, left alone.
Length ball outside off, swinging in. Labuschagne leaves it alone.

FOUR! What a shot to get to your half ton! Bouncer way outside off, Labuschagne gets high on his toes and upper cuts it over the slip cordon and into the third man fence. A crucial knock at a crucial time from Labuschagne.
Bouncer this time outside off, Smith chooses to leave it alone.
Way wide outside off, swinging even further away. Smith leaves it alone.

On the pads, Labuschagne works this one towards the mid-wicket region for a single. This brings up the 50-run stand between Smith and Labuschagne. Both of these batters are looking strong in the middle and will be aiming to go big now.
On off this time, Labuschagne powers it to the man at mid off.
Good length ball on off, driven towards mid on.

Length ball on middle, Labuschagne shuffles and looks to work this one towards the leg side but misses to get hit on the thigh pad. The ball rolls towards the leg side and the batters opt against the run.
The umpires have gone for a run out check for Marnus Labuschagne. He looks well in. Let's see what the replays have to show.

NOT OUT! Labuschagne was a little lazy in getting his bat down in time but gets in safely. Full delivery on middle, Labuschagne flicks it to mid-wicket and takes off for a single. Nicholls throws it to the bowler's end and hits. Labuschagne tumbles while getting inside the crease but looks well in. The umpire refers to the third umpire to check and the replays show that Labuschagne has made it inside the crease.
Very full delivery on middle and leg, Labuschagne pushes it to mid off.
Fullish ball in the channel outside off, Marnus makes a leave to the keeper.
On a length on middle, Marnus works it to square leg and takes a single.
Fullish delivery outside off, Smith lets the ball go to the keeper.
Back of a length delivery on off, Smith defends it out off the back foot to cover.
Lockie Ferguson is back into the attack. 7-1-31-0 are his figures so far.
Length ball way outside off, Labuschagne goes chasing after it. He swings his bat at it but misses the ball completely.
Another length ball, this time on the leg side. Labuschagne does well to defend it.
A bit fuller this time, Labuschagne comes on the front foot and defends.
Length ball on middle and off, defended by Marnus.

This time a much stronger appeal but again nothing from the umpire. Length ball on middle and off, Labuschagne looks to prod forward and defend but misses to get hit high on the pad again. Southee and the Kiwi players appeal but the umpire is again unmoved. Southee asks Williamson about taking the review but the skipper feels it is way too high. Replays roll in and show that Williamson was right as the ball would be missing the stumps by a huge margin.

Length ball around middle and leg, Labuschagne looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pad. Southee puts in a stifled appeal but the umpire is unmoved. New Zealand do not mull over taking the review. Replays and Ball Tracker show that the ball was going above the middle stump.
Smith prods forward and pushes this one towards cover.
Smith goes back in his crease and defends it towards the off side.
Floated ball on off, driven towards the man at mid off.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
FOUR! Beautiful from Smith! Floated ball right near the foot of Smith, he whips it through the narrow gap between short mid-wicket and mid on and the ball races away to the fence.
Shortish ball just outside off, pushed towards point.
Another one way outside off, left alone by Labuschagne. 8 runs off the over.
FOUR! Cracking shot! Length ball outside off, Labuschagne rocks back and cuts this one through backward point for a boundary.

This is a very important part of the session, day, inning, match and perhaps the series for New Zealand. They have worked so hard post Lunch, not picking up wickets but building up sustained pressure. They would not want to give it away through frustration by bowling inconsistent lines. If these two get off the hook, this will slip away pretty quickly.
On the leg side again, this time Steven works it fine for a single.
Good length ball outside off, pushed towards cover.
Length ball outside off, Smith leaves it alone.
Back of a length ball on the hips, Labuschagne goes back and pulls it towards deep square leg for three.
Tim Southee returns. 9-2-16-0 so far.
Landed outside off, well - what is that? A NORMAL LEAVE FROM SMITH! Rare, very rare. Lunges and then shoulders arms.
Full and outside off, defended from the crease.
On middle and off, tucked through mid-wicket.
Around off, defended watchfully.
On middle, flicked towards short leg.
Tossed up wide outside off, Smith leans and drives it towards short cover.

DRINKS BREAK. A boring hour but a testing one for the batsmen. The Kiwis have been disciplined, keeping the batters under check and giving nothing away. Just 34 runs in 16 overs since Lunch. But Smith and Labuschagne have done well too, not throwing it away. Yet. But Smith has shown signs of frustration with the ball not quite coming onto the bat.
Well outside off, left alone.
Full and outside off, Marnus drives this straight back as an arrow but de Grandhomme does well to get his hand down to deflect it towards mid off.
FOUR! Slightly wrong in line and punished. Full and down the leg side, Labuschagne tickles it to the fine leg fence.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Very full outside off, dug out towards cover.
Full and outside off, left alone.
Flatter and on off, Smith punches to covers off the back foot.
Flatter on off, defended back to the bowler.
Full and outside off, defended towards covers.
Flatter and on the pads, Marnus nudges it towards square leg for a run.
Tossed up around off, defended to the leg side.
Floated outside off, Marnus drives it to mid off.
Mitchell Santner is back on. 3-0-12-0 so far.
Good length ball outside off, Smith lets the ball go to the keeper in his trademark style.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length ball on middle, Smith defends it back to de Grandhomme.
FOUR! Poor ball! Good length ball on the pads, Smith just helps it on its way with an angled bat to the fine leg region for a boundary.
Full delivery on middle, Smith drives it back to the bowler.

Full delivery outside off, very rarely you see Smith play a rash shot. This time he loses his shape but still manages to play a drive to a ball which he could have left alone. The ball rolls to mid off.

Interesting observation from Mark 'Junior' Waugh. The former batsman says that Smith has not looked at his absolute ease today. He has been checking his shots a lot. Waugh draws an inference that perhaps, the pitch is on the slower side and the ball is not coming onto the bat that easily.
Labuschagne defends this good length ball on off to mid off.
Good length ball in the channel outside off, ML does not fiddle with it and leaves it alone.
Back of a length delivery on off, Smith guides it to gully and takes a single.
BOUNCER! Wagner bowls this around middle stump, Smith does well to duck under it.
Fullish delivery outside off, Smith drives it to mid off and shouts a loud wait on.
Full delivery on middle, Smith whips it to mid-wicket.
Full delivery on middle, Marnus plays it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length ball on middle, Smith tucks it to the leg side and takes a single. 100 up for Australia.
On a length outside off, Steven lets the ball go to the keeper.
Very full delivery on off, Smith solidly defends it back to the bowler.
Fullish ball on middle, Smith drives it to mid on.
Full delivery on middle, Marnus looks to flick it but it goes off the inside half of the bat towards deep square leg. The batters pick up a single.
Good length ball on off, Smith punches it to cover for nothing.
Wagner bowls a full ball in the channel outside off, Smith leaves it alone.
Short delivery outside off, Labuschagne cuts it to deep cover and picks up a single.
Fullish delivery outside off, Marnus drives it but finds the cover fielder who collects it on a bounce.
Wagner bowls a full one on off, Marnus blocks it towards mid off.
Full delivery way outside off, it is too wide to make Labuschagne play at it as he lets the ball go to the keeper.
Full ball on off, Smith solidly defends it this time to mid off.
BEATEN! Full delivery outside off tailing away a bit, Smith looks to block it but misses it.
On off, defended out.
Smith pushes this full delivery back to the bowler.
Full delivery on middle, Smith tucks it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball outside off, Smith lets the ball go to the keeper.
Driven towards the mid on region.
A knuckle ball, extremely full, almost a yorker bowled at 111.9 kph, on middle stump. Marnus does really well to block it out.
Another full delivery outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms to this one.
Fullish ball outside the off stump line, Marnus does not feel the need to play at it and leaves it alone.
Short ball on middle, Steven rocks on his back foot and pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Smith flicks it to mid-wicket for nothing.
Good length ball on off, Labuschagne blocks it out to the off side.
