Outside off, Watling shoulders arms to this one.
Flighted delivery on off, Nicholls plays it towards point for a single.
Tossed up delivery on off, Nicholls defends it off the back foot.
Around middle, worked through mid-wicket for a single.
Marnus Labuschagne comes into the attack.
Floated delivery on middle, Nicholls looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Loopy delivery on middle, Henry defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Henry blocks it well.
Flighted delivery on off, Nicholls plays it to covers.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Nicholls looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Short delivery on off, Nicholls makes room and slaps it to covers but Marnus Labuschagne dives to his right and makes a stunning stop.
Good length delivery on off, BJ blocks it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, Watling defends it off the front foot.
Length delivery on off, Watling taps it towards gully where Warner makes a fine stop with a dive.
A bouncer on middle, BJ ducks.
Similar line, probably a bit more on off, watchfully defended.
Full and outside off, driven beautifully but straight back to Cummins who deflects it to mid off off his left hand.

Loopy delivery on off, Nicholls looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head. Tim Paine has a chat with his bowler who straightaway indicates there was an inside edge on that one. Replays confirm.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Nicholls keeps it out.
Flighted delivery on off, Nicholls blocks it well.
Floated delivery on middle, Watling nudges it towards square leg for a run.
Short delivery outside off, Nicholls makes room and slaps it through covers. The fielder from long off does well to stop it. The batsmen get three runs.
Tossed up delivery on off, Nicholls defends it out.
So Nathan Lyon is not going to bowl unchanged in this session. Here comes Travis Head to bowl his offies.
Good length delivery on off, Watling offers a solid defense on this one.
Short delivery on leg, Nicholls pulls it towards fine leg for a run.
On a good length on off, Henry defends it off the front foot.
Full and outside off, angling in, Nicholls shoulders arms.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Around off, solidly defended.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Outside off, driven straight to mid off.

Full and around middle, Watling lunges and flicks it towards the leg side. Matthew Wade at short leg dives to his left and flicks it immediately at the stumps. Tim Paine misses it but Steven Smith at first slip stops it. Wade apologizes to his skipper.
This time he is on his back foot to defend.
Around off, solidly defended.
FOUR! A rare bad ball. Short and outside off, Watling rocks back and cuts it through the covers.

EDGED, BUT DOES NOT CARRY! Paine smiles. Perfect from Cummins, landing it on a length outside off and drawing Nicholls forward. The outside edge is induced but for some reason it lands in front of Tim Paine.
Too full and a bit too straight. Nicholls flicks it through mid-wicket and gets a couple. Moves to 10 and the stand is worth 20 from 33 balls.
Landed outside off, left alone.
Around off, pushed towards cover.
Landed outside off, watchfully defended towards cover.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Gets it past Wade this time for a run.
That is a very good stop. Around off, Nicholls tucks it through the leg side but Matthew Wade at short leg does well to stop it.
Landed outside off, punched towards cover.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
A short ball outside off, Nicholls looks to pull but misses. Paine fumbles behind.
Landed outside off, dabbed towards gully.
Similar line and length, this time BJW is perfect in his forward defense.

Very good bowling. Cummins understands that Watling would be expecting a short ball, so bowls it fuller. BJ is late in bringing his bat down to defend and is beaten, with the ball moving away late to beat the outside edge, almost like a leg spinner.

The physio is out in the middle. Watling looks okay and just changes his helmet. The normal procedure going through. This is taking a bit too long. The Kiwis are making sure that the helmet of Latham is well protected, hence that extra padding is going on. Trent Boult is also amongst the ones helping.

ON THE HELMET! First up, Watling is okay and signals a thumbs up. That just kept on rising. On a length outside off, Watling looks to defend but the ball suddenly kicks up, goes past his gloves and hits him on the grille of his helmet. He walks away immediately and when Cummins asks about his health, he indicates he is fine.
FOUR! Landed outside off, Watling looks to defend but the ball goes off the outside edge, along the ground, past second slip towards third man.
Outside off, on a length, left alone.
Pat Cummins returns. Runs have come at a premium off his bowling. 8-4-10-0 so far.
Full and around off, Nicholls lunges and blocks it down the track.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Landed outside off, the arm ball, left alone.
FOUR! A rare boundary. You need to punish the bad balls. Short and outside off, Nicholls rocks back and pulls it through mid-wicket.
Outside off, played towards point.
Around off, blocked from the crease.
DRINKS BREAK. A good end to that hour for Australia. Starc got Taylor and then Lyon got Latham. Two big guns. The Test is rapidly progressing and another wicket could lead to a procession.
On a good length on middle, Watling defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Watling offers no shot to this one.
Full delivery on off, Watling drives it through covers. The batsmen get two runs.
Bowls a bouncer outside off, Watling sways away from it.
FOUR! What a shot! Full delivery on leg, Watling flicks it through square leg for a boundary.
Length delivery on middle, Nicholls flicks it through square leg. Lyon runs and does well to stop it. The batsmen get three runs.
Outside off, BJ hangs back to defend.
Down the leg side, helped towards square leg.
Full and outside off, Watling dead-bats it.
BJ Watling walks in next, at number 6, replacing Latham. Another man who can bat for hours.

OUT! LBW! That is plumb and Aleem Dar has to overturn the decision! Lyon has his second. The arm ball does the trick. Pitched around off, Latham stays back to defend but misses it as the ball skids off the deck. He is caught in his crease and is hit on the pads. Lyon immediately roars but umpire Dar shakes his head. Tim Paine has a long chat with his bowler and when it seems like both are not convinced whether that would be out, he signals for the review. Ball Tracker shows it to be hitting leg stump and one man who could have stayed for hours at the crease, departs.

Massive shout for LBW! Is Latham plumb in front? Umpire Aleem Dar has not agreed. Paine has a long chat with his bowler and with 8 seconds left on the DRS clock, takes the review. Looks close. Yup. Ball Tracker shows it to be hitting leg!
Tossed up delivery on middle, Latham comes down the track and blocks it.
Flighted delivery on middle, Latham defends it off the front foot.
Outside off, played straight to point.
Around middle, pushed towards short mid-wicket.
Henry Nicholls walks in at number 5, replacing Taylor.

OUT! Caught behind! There goes Rosco. Starc has struck. His second wicket. Taylor, looking to play his natural game, has perished. The ball is not much different from the second one in this over. The length is short and Rosco thinks that he can pull across the line. He does so but perhaps this one comes quicker than his anticipation. Takes the under edge and goes behind, with Tim Paine completing the formalities. Another massive blow.
Bowls it down the leg side, Taylor lets it go.
Short of a length delivery on middle, Taylor pulls it towards mid-wicket where the fielder makes a fine stop.
Length delivery on leg, Taylor looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad. It goes towards the keeper safely.
Full delivery on middle, Taylor drives it through mid on for a run.
Floated delivery on off, Taylor looks to play a reverse sweep but misses it and gets hit on the boot.
Flighted delivery on off, Taylor defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Latham plays that very late and guides it towards short third man. The batsmen take a run.

That is fired down the leg side. 92.5 kph, Latham looks to sweep but misses it. Tim Paine behind just about manages to get his glove to stop that. Immediately wrings his hands in pain. That would have hurt.
Short delivery on middle, Latham looks to pull but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On a good length on middle, Latham looks to flick but gets it off the inner half of the bat. It goes towards fine leg for a single.
On a length on middle, Latham flicks it through square leg. The batsmen get two runs.

Full delivery outside off, Taylor drives it through covers. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it before the ropes. The batsmen get three runs. Good running between the wickets. 50 UP FOR NEW ZEALAND.
Good length delivery on middle, Ross defends it off the back foot.
Rash shot. On a good length on off, Taylor looks to drive, without moving his feet and gets a bottom edge, which goes on the bounce to the bowler.
Full delivery on middle, Taylor defends it to mid-wicket.
Mitchell Starc is back on. 6-2-17-1 so far.
Flighted delivery on middle, Latham keeps it out.
Short delivery outside off, Latham cuts it to point.
Loopy delivery on middle, Tom looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.

Oohhh... a bit too early. Floated delivery on middle, Latham comes down the track and looks to flick but is beaten in flight. Luckily for him, the ball hits his pads. Lyon spotted pretty early that Latham was off his blocks. Hence, fired it in.
Flighted delivery on middle, Latham blocks it off the front foot.
The arm ball outside off, left alone.
Good length delivery on off, Ross defends it off the front foot.
BEATEN! Beauty of a delivery! On a good length and outside off, Rosco looks to defend but the ball pitches and then seams away, to beat the outside edge.
WIDE! A wild bouncer, around middle and leg, comfortably ducked under. It is not even a proper duck. The bouncer was so high.
Short of a length delivery outside off, Taylor looks to pull but misses it.
Length delivery on middle, Ross flicks it through square leg. The batsmen pick up a couple.
Good length delivery on off, Taylor plays it to covers.
On a good length on middle, Taylor defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Latham defends it off the back foot.
Loopy delivery on off, Latham keeps it out.
Floated delivery on off, Taylor sweeps it through mid-wicket for a run.
Square leg is now being shifted. He gets squarer. Long on moves right slightly.

FOUR! AUDACIOUS! Taylor is ready for the challenge. Flighted outside off, Rosco gets down and mows the slog sweep. There is a deep square leg in place but this is played in front of him, towards mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, Rosco looks to defend but gets a bottom edge, on the bounce over the keeper to first slip.
Full and around off, worked in front of short leg.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Latham looks to defend but misses it.
Another LBW appeal but turned down. On a good length on leg, Latham looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head.
Bowls a bumper, Latham ducks under it.
Outside off, TL leaves it alone.
Good length delivery on off, Tom defends it off the back foot.
On a good length on middle, Latham nudges it towards the leg side.
FOUR! Nice shot. Tossed up delivery on middle, Taylor plays a slog sweep over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Floated delivery on middle, Latham flicks it towards mid-wicket. The batsmen cross ends.
Loopy delivery on off, Tom blocks it well.
Flighted delivery on middle, Ross flicks it towards square leg for a single.
Tossed up delivery on off, Rosco defends it back towards the bowler.
Floated delivery on middle, Taylor flicks it to short fine leg.
Bowls a bouncer on leg, TL does well to duck under it.
Good length delivery on off, Tom blocks it off the front foot.
On a good length on off, Latham defends it off the back foot.
Short delivery on leg, Taylor looks to pull but gets it off the glove. It goes towards fine leg for a run. That hurried onto Taylor.
Outside off, Rosco offers no shot to this one.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Taylor looks to defend but misses it.
Short delivery on off, Latham makes room and cuts it through point. The batsmen get two runs.
Flighted delivery on middle, well kept out again.
Short delivery on off, Latham cuts it to point.
Floated delivery on middle, TL defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Tom defends it out.
Flighted delivery outside off, Latham offers no shot to this one.
Nathan Lyon to bowl from the other end. Will he bowl unchanged through this session? 2-0-8-1 so far.
On a length outside off, Rosco looks to defend but misses.
Outside off, on a length, Taylor looks to defend but then aims to take his bat away. Is late and the ball goes off the bottom edge, on the bounce, to gully.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat. One run added to the total.

Huge appeal for LBW now! Turned down again! Will the Australians review? Cummins looks interested. Tim Paine walks towards Nathan Lyon at point to talk about the height and then does not take the review. A length ball outside off, hits a crack and stays a touch low. Latham is hit on his back foot and seems to fall over a touch. It looks close to the naked eye but Ball Tracker shows it to be going over the top. Superb decision from Nigel Llong and excellent call from Nathan Lyon at point to tell Paine not to review. He would have been at the best angle to see where the ball would have hit.

Huge appeal for a caught behind! Turned down by umpire Llong. No warm-ups for Cummins. No looseners. He comes running in and lands it on a length outside off, making it to jag back in. Tom looks to defend but misses. The ball goes off something to the keeper and the slip cordon explodes. Llong is unmoved. Replays show that the ball hit the back thigh. Superb decision.
Full and around off, bounces sharply but Latham is solid in defense.

Out come the players onto the field. Pat Cummins it will be to start off proceedings after the break. 4 overs in his pre-Lunch spell. How many will he bowl in this one? Tom Latham to face. Here we go...

Welcome back for the second session. Normally, with the pitch opening up as it already has, one would assume this to be the final session of the match. But because this is a Day-Night game, ironically, this is the best time to bat. Can the Kiwis get a partnership and keep the Aussies at bay? Their first aim should be to tire out Starc and Cummins, so that Paine is forced to resort to Wade and Labuschagne.
... DAY 4, SESSION 2 ...

Now, 8 wickets to take for the Aussies. Can they finish it off on the fourth day itself? Or have the Kiwis got them in to battle out the heat and the pitch to take the game on the fifth day? We will find that out soon. Join us for the second session after the break.

He tells that he was happy to see Lyon get a wicket and would've loved to see him get a hat-trick. Tells that Taylor was brilliant in the first innings but Lyon is bowling well. Hopes that he along with Starc look to assist the spinner.

As far as the Aussies are concerned, Starc and Cummins were superb with the ball early on. Starc was rewarded with a wicket while Lyon with the help of the pitch removed the mighty wicket of Williamson. While they are a bowler short, the variable bounce on the pitch are surely there to assist them. Playing against Lyon on this track is going to be tricky. Interesting to see if the Kiwis battle it out and take the game on the fifth day. Before that, Cummins is caught for the chat.

New Zealand has 1 hour to survive before the Lunch break. They have lost two already which includes the massive wicket of Kiwi skipper Williamson. Latham is looking solid and he has Taylor for company. These two are going to be the key for New Zealand. Taylor scored a solid 80 in the first innings and he might have to double that total if the Kiwis are to force or draw or maybe attempt to win the game.
Landed outside off, Taylor shoulders arms and is hit on the thighs. Paine puts in a mild shout for LBW but is not entertained. LUNCH ON DAY 4!
Full and on middle, Latham pushes this wide of substitute Michael Neser at mid on and pinches a quick run.
Short and outside off, cut behind point for a couple.
Tossed up outside off, RT drives it to the left of mid off and takes a single.
Oohh... full and outside off, Rosco looks to drive but the ball spins in and takes the inside edge onto the pads. Lobs up but is nowhere near first slip.
Around off, fuller in length, Taylor stays back and defends.
Down the leg side, left alone.
In the air... safe! Landed around leg, Taylor looks to flick but the ball goes uppishly, wide of Marnus Labuschagne at leg gully. A single to fine leg. Wait a second. Leg bye signalled.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
On a length, around off, Rosco looks to defend and then aims to take his bat away. Is late and gets beaten.
A length ball, around middle, Latham looks to flick but gets a leading edge towards cover. A single taken.
Down the leg side, left alone.
Full and around off, watchfully played out.
Around off, blocked from the crease.
FOUR! Edged away! Full and wide outside off, Taylor reaches out to drive but gets a thick outside edge which flies behind backward point. Off the mark in streaky fashion.
Full and outside off, watchfully played out again.
No hat-trick. Full and outside off, Taylor lunges and defends.

Ross Taylor comes in at number 4. Can he ensure that at least 8 wickets are in the bank going into Lunch? Also, LYON IS ON A HAT-TRICK. He dismissed Southee on the final ball of the first innings and now Williamson, with his very first ball in this innings. Here we go...

OUT! Turn and bounce, caught at short leg! That is a huge, huge wicket with 10 minutes to go to Lunch. Kane Williamson is gone. Nothing much he could have done there. The pitch has consumed him. Accurate Lyon lands this right on the rough outside off, around a shorter length. Williamson stays back to tuck but the ball lands on that black mark, generates dust and kicks off suddenly. Zooms in, takes the inside edge, hits the thigh and lobs to Matthew Wade at short leg. The Aussies celebrate and even before the appeal can be completed, Aleem Dar's finger is up. They check for the overstepping but Lyon is fine. Williamson walks back disappointed but to be fair, there was nothing much he could have done to that ball.
Well, Gaza is here. Or Gary. Official name - Nathan Lyon.
Full and straight, pushed down the ground. Substitute Michael Neser gets across from short mid-wicket and stops the ball.
Nathan Lyon is warming up...
Landed outside off, slightly wider, let through once more.
Full and straight, watchfully defended in front of mid on.
Outside off, left alone again.
Around off, Tom looks to defend but takes his bat inside the line.

Gone? Caught behind? Tim Paine starts to celebrate and then appeals but umpire Nigel Llong is unmoved. No review taken. Landed around off, Latham looks to defend but the ball moves away slightly and goes behind. Hard to pick any noise on first look or hear. Snickometer detects nothing when the ball goes past the bat.
Landed outside off, left alone.

FOUR! ELEGANT! Williamson is off to a flier! His third boundary in just 6 balls faced. Full and outside off, Williamson leans and drives it through the covers. Interestingly, replays show that Williamson turned his bat in his hands before facing the ball.
Full and straight, swinging away, defended back to the bowler.
Around middle, tucked through short leg for a single.
Full and outside off, watchfully patted down the track.
Full and outside off, left alone.
Fuller length on off, Williamson defends it out. End of a successful over from Starc.
Around off on a length, Williamson tucks it through gully to pick a couple.
FOUR! On the pads again from Starc. Williamson flicks it nicely through square leg to get another boundary. Starc is attempting an inswinging yorker but misses out.
FOUR! Easily put away! Starc looks to welcome the Kiwi skipper with a yorker but ends up dishing a full toss on the pads. Williamson flicks it to the deep square leg fence to get off the mark.
Skipper Kane Williamson walks in next. Around 25 minutes left, can the Aussies get rid of the big wicket?

OUT! Caught at point! Starc strikes and the poor run for Raval in Tests continues. Australia draw first blood. This is just behind the good length area but on off. Raval comes forward and looks to defend. The ball takes the outside edge and goes straight to Lyon at point. He is not going to drop these. Raval shakes his head as he walks off.
Shortish length ball outside off, Raval lets it be.
Full and on the pads, Latham clips it towards the leg side nicely but Head makes another excellent stop at short leg.
Fullish this time and on off stump line, Latham is once again solid in the defense as he pushes it towards mid off.
No, not really as he goes short around off, Latham blocks it off the back foot.

Wow! That kept low. We might get one sneak through. A good length ball on off, keeps very low. Latham does well to dig it out. Cummins smiles as looks at the spot where the ball pitched. Aiming to pitch there again?
Around off, Latham is solid in his defense once again.
Outside off, left alone.
Another back of a length ball outside off, Raval lets it be. A few words from Starc to Raval there.
Shortish and closer to off, Raval covers his stumps, drops his wrists and lets it be.
Good length ball around off, Raval at the last moment taps it towards fourth slip.
Good length ball around off, Raval taps it towards cover.
Shortish length ball outside off. Raval is not bothered as he shoulders arms.
Back of a length ball on middle, Latham tucks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Full and on off, Raval defends it out solidly.
Fullish but wide outside off, Raval makes another leave.
Goes back to bowling in the corridor outside off. Raval lets it be.
This time Cummins lands it on off, Raval looks to defend but gets an outside edge.
Full and around off, Raval drives it well but cannot beat Wade at short extra cover.
Good length ball outside off, Raval has his stumps covered as he shoulders arms.
Bouncer on middle this time. Latham ducks under it to see off the over.
Landed on middle, Latham goes back and defends it out.
On middle, Latham pushes it towards mid on.

Interesting. Adam Gilchrist on air says that there is some rain predicted for Monday. Temperatures are forecast to be 35 degrees Celsius. Mark Waugh jokes that better get some jackets while coming then.
Fuller and on off, Latham defends it towards mid off.
In the channel outside off, Latham covers his stumps and lets it be. Carries to Paine at a perfect height behind the wicket.
Brilliant work from Head at short leg. A good length ball on the pads, Latham looks to tuck it towards square leg but Head moves to his left and stops it nicely.
That hit the crack and kept low! It is a fullish ball, the ones which are driveable. Raval is caught in two minds. As he first looks to drive but at the last moment draws his bat back.
Shortish length ball just outside off, Raval sways away form it.
Good length ball outside off, Raval makes a leave.
On middle, angled in. Raval defends it out.
Outside off, left alone.

Huge appeal for caught behind but looks like it came off the pads. Cummins is right on the money first ball. Lands it on middle and leg, Raval looks to tuck it around but gets hit on the flap of his pad. The ball goes the slip cordon. Warner from gully comes ahead and takes the catch. The Aussies appeal but nothing from the umpire. The replays confirm no bat.
Pat Cummins to bowl from the other end. Just a wicket for him in the first innings. Can he get one in this session?
Shortish length ball just outside off, Latham rides the bounce and taps it towards the off side.

FOUR! Punched nicely! Fuller ball on middle and leg, Latham closes his bat face and punches it past diving sub fielder Neser at short mid-wicket. It races towards the long on fence. Neser gives it a chase but the ball wins the race. First boundary of the innings.
In the channel outside off again. Latham shoulders arms.
Fullish length ball just outside off, left alone.
Raval and New Zealand are underway! Starc bowls on the pads of the left-hander. Raval tucks it towards square leg and takes a singe.
Starc starts with a good length ball outside off, making it shape away just a hint. Raval lets it be.
